    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5352" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κλέος</span></b>  (root <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κλυ, κλύω</span>), pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κλέᾱ</span> (shortened before a vowel): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">rumor, tidings,
            glory;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σόν, ἐμὸν κλέος</span>, ‘news of thee,’ ‘of
          me,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 13.415</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; κλέος πρὸς Τρώων</span>, ‘an honor to thee
          before the Trojans,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 22.415</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀνδρῶν κλέᾱ</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">glorious
            deeds</span> (laudes), <i><span class="en">Il.
          9.189</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
